#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:4
msgid "Testing with Brownie"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:6
msgid ""
"`Brownie <https://github.com/iamdefinitelyahuman/brownie>`_ is a Python-"
"based development and testing framework for smart contracts. It includes a "
"pytest plugin with fixtures that simplify testing your contract."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:8
msgid ""
"This section provides a quick overview of testing with Brownie. To learn "
"more, you can view the Brownie documentation on `writing unit tests <https://"
"eth-brownie.readthedocs.io/en/stable/tests-pytest-intro.html>`_ or join the "
"`Ethereum Python Dev Discord <https://discord.gg/abJEARdx3Q>`_ ``#brownie`` "
"channel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:11
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:13
msgid ""
"In order to use Brownie for testing you must first `initialize a new project "
"<https://eth-brownie.readthedocs.io/en/stable/init.html>`_. Create a new "
"directory for the project, and from within that directory type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:15
msgid "$ brownie init"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:19
msgid ""
"This will create an empty `project structure <https://eth-brownie."
"readthedocs.io/en/stable/structure.html#structure>`_ within the directory. "
"Store your contract sources within the project's ``contracts/`` directory "
"and your tests within ``tests/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:22
msgid "Writing a Basic Test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:24
msgid ""
"Assume the following simple contract ``Storage.vy``. It has a single integer "
"variable and a function to set that value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:26
msgid "storage.vy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:26
msgid ""
"#pragma version >0.3.10\n"
"\n"
"storedData: public(int128)\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(_x: int128):\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def set(_x: int128):\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:31
msgid ""
"We create a test file ``tests/test_storage.py`` where we write our tests in "
"pytest style."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:33
msgid "test_storage.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:33
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"INITIAL_VALUE = 4\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def storage_contract(Storage, accounts):\n"
"    # deploy the contract with the initial value as a constructor argument\n"
"    yield Storage.deploy(INITIAL_VALUE, {'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_initial_state(storage_contract):\n"
"    # Check if the constructor of the contract is set up properly\n"
"    assert storage_contract.storedData() == INITIAL_VALUE\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_set(storage_contract, accounts):\n"
"    # set the value to 10\n"
"    storage_contract.set(10, {'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"    assert storage_contract.storedData() == 10  # Directly access "
"storedData\n"
"\n"
"    # set the value to -5\n"
"    storage_contract.set(-5, {'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"    assert storage_contract.storedData() == -5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:63
msgid ""
"In this example we are using two fixtures which are provided by Brownie:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:65
msgid ""
"``accounts`` provides access to the :py:class:`Accounts <brownie.network."
"account.Accounts>` container, containing all of your local accounts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:66
msgid ""
"``Storage`` is a dynamically named fixture that provides access to a :py:"
"class:`ContractContainer <brownie.network.contract.ContractContainer>` "
"object, used to deploy your contract"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:70
msgid ""
"To run the tests, use the ``brownie test`` command from the root directory "
"of your project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:73
msgid "Testing Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:75
msgid ""
"For the remaining examples, we expand our simple storage contract to include "
"an event and two conditions for a failed transaction: ``advanced_storage.vy``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:77
msgid "advanced_storage.vy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:77
msgid ""
"#pragma version >0.3.10\n"
"\n"
"event DataChange:\n"
"    setter: indexed(address)\n"
"    value: int128\n"
"\n"
"storedData: public(int128)\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(_x: int128):\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def set(_x: int128):\n"
"  assert _x >= 0, \"No negative values\"\n"
"  assert self.storedData < 100, \"Storage is locked when 100 or more is "
"stored\"\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
"  log DataChange(setter=msg.sender, value=_x)\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def reset():\n"
"  self.storedData = 0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:82
msgid ""
"To test events, we examine the :py:class:`TransactionReceipt <brownie."
"network.transaction.TransactionReceipt>` object which is returned after each "
"successful transaction. It contains an :py:class:`events <brownie.network."
"event.EventDict>` member with information about events that fired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:84
msgid ""
"import brownie\n"
"\n"
"INITIAL_VALUE = 4\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def adv_storage_contract(AdvancedStorage, accounts):\n"
"    yield AdvancedStorage.deploy(INITIAL_VALUE, {'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"\n"
"def test_events(adv_storage_contract, accounts):\n"
"    tx1 = adv_storage_contract.set(10, {'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"    tx2 = adv_storage_contract.set(20, {'from': accounts[1]})\n"
"    tx3 = adv_storage_contract.reset({'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"\n"
"    # Check log contents\n"
"    assert len(tx1.events) == 1\n"
"    assert tx1.events[0]['value'] == 10\n"
"\n"
"    assert len(tx2.events) == 1\n"
"    assert tx2.events[0]['setter'] == accounts[1]\n"
"\n"
"    assert not tx3.events   # tx3 does not generate a log"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:112
msgid "Handling Reverted Transactions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:114
msgid ""
"Transactions that revert raise a :py:class:`VirtualMachineError <brownie."
"exceptions.VirtualMachineError>` exception. To write assertions around this "
"you can use :py:class:`brownie.reverts <brownie.test.plugin."
"RevertContextManager>` as a context manager. It functions very similarly to :"
"py:func:`pytest.raises <pytest.raises>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:116
msgid ""
":py:class:`brownie.reverts <brownie.test.plugin.RevertContextManager>` "
"optionally accepts a string as an argument. If given, the error string "
"returned by the transaction must match it in order for the test to pass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../testing-contracts-brownie.rst:119
msgid ""
"import brownie\n"
"\n"
"INITIAL_VALUE = 4\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def adv_storage_contract(AdvancedStorage, accounts):\n"
"    yield AdvancedStorage.deploy(INITIAL_VALUE, {'from': accounts[0]})\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_failed_transactions(adv_storage_contract, accounts):\n"
"    # Try to set the storage to a negative amount\n"
"    with brownie.reverts(\"No negative values\"):\n"
"        adv_storage_contract.set(-10, {\"from\": accounts[1]})\n"
"\n"
"    # Lock the contract by storing more than 100. Then try to change the "
"value\n"
"\n"
"    adv_storage_contract.set(150, {\"from\": accounts[1]})\n"
"    with brownie.reverts(\"Storage is locked when 100 or more is stored\"):\n"
"        adv_storage_contract.set(10, {\"from\": accounts[1]})\n"
"\n"
"    # Reset the contract and try to change the value\n"
"    adv_storage_contract.reset({\"from\": accounts[1]})\n"
"    adv_storage_contract.set(10, {\"from\": accounts[1]})\n"
"    assert adv_storage_contract.storedData() == 10"
msgstr ""
